<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-NOTES-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GAILEY SAYS HE STILL TRUSTS HIS KICKER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CHAREAN WILLIAMS 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Dallas Cowboys coach Chan Gailey said he still
has confidence in kicker Richie Cunningham.
</P>
<P>
   But his confidence extends only so far.
</P>
<P>
   In the 20-0 victory on Thanksgiving Day, the Cowboys went for it
on fourth down _ and failed _ on two possessions inside the
Dolphins' 40-yard line. Gailey passed on having Cunningham attempt
field goals of 52 and 53 yards.
</P>
<P>
   Cunningham has made 10 of 19 field-goal attempts this season,
including 3-of-9 from beyond 39 yards. In his career, Cunningham is
2-for-5 from beyond 50 yards.
</P>
<P>
   Gailey said Monday that 40-45 yards is within Cunningham's
range.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm a little bit more wary about putting him out there in some
of those situations (50-53 yards),'' Gailey said. YELLOW FLAGGED
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys have the second-most penalties and the most penalty
yards in the NFL. They have drawn 95 penalties for 872 yards.
Cincinnati's 98 penalties leads the league, and the Bengals rank
second to the Cowboys with 782 penalty yards.
</P>
<P>
   ``You impress upon our guys the importance of not having them,''
Chan Gailey said. ``The one thing that upsets you the most as a
coach is the presnap penalties, and those have not been drastically
bad. It's been the postsnap penalties that have hurt us the most
this year. All you can tell them is watch your hands, watch what
you do, make good decisions on the field. But you don't want to
take away from their aggressiveness.'' HARPER'S BIZARRE SEASON
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys have not seen enough of Alvin Harper to know if he
can help their banged-up receiving corps. Harper, who has not
caught a pass since Sept. 28, 1997, has been active for only two
games and has played in only one since signing on Oct. 14 for the
prorated veteran minimum of $400,000.
</P>
<P>
   In the fourth quarter of the Cowboys' 38-20 victory against the
Redskins, Harper dropped a pass and drew a 17-yard pass
interference penalty.
</P>
<P>
   He was inactive for the Thanksgiving Day game against the
Dolphins after pulling his left quadricep in practice two days
earlier. Harper is questionable for Sunday's game against New
England.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm just here doing what they want me to do, working and
getting in shape,'' Harper said. ``Hopefully in the next week or
so, I can get in there and get a chance to do something.'' NO WORD
</P>
<P>
   Chan Gailey said the team is no closer to receiving a definitive
answer from Michael Irvin about his future. Irvin, who caught 10
passes for 167 yards and three touchdowns in four games, remains on
the 53-player roster despite his cervical contusion/genetic
condition.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think that that time will come when it needs to come,''
Gailey said. INJURY UPDATE
</P>
<P>
   Cowboys left guard Larry Allen will miss his third consecutive
game with a sprained medical collateral ligament in his right knee.
Cornerback Kevin Mathis (left hamstring) is doubtful, and Harper,
fullback Ryan Neufeld (right ankle), cornerback Kevin Smith (right
hamstring) and center Mark Stepnoski (left calf) are questionable.
Safety Chris Akins (right groin) and running back Emmitt Smith
(right hand) are probable. nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-11-30-99 0048EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19991130.0016 </DOCNO>
