<HEADLINE>
RE-SIGNING SELE IS PRIORITY, RANGERS GM SAYS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By T.R. SULLIVAN 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas _ Texas Rangers general manager Doug Melvin
said he feels like television host Regis Philbin.
</P>
<P>
   ``I sitting here asking players, `Who wants to be a
millionaire?' '' Melvin said. ``The only thing is they don't have
to answer any questions.''
</P>
<P>
   They do have to say yes or no, and Melvin would like to see a
starting pitcher say yes this week, preferably right-hander Aaron
Sele. A month has passed this off-season and there has yet to be a
significant free-agent signing in baseball, especially among
starting pitchers.
</P>
<P>
   It was about this time last year that Randy Johnson agreed to a
four-year, $52.4 million contract with the Arizona Diamondbacks, a
move that resulted in the Rangers signing Rafael Palmeiro to a
five-year, $45 million contract.
</P>
<P>
   But the relative quiet on this year's free-agent front
reinforces that it is a weak group with no one star worth pursuing
at all costs.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think people are waiting for one guy to sign,'' Melvin said.
``Then they can say, `If that guy's worth so much money, then my
guy is worth this much money.' ''
</P>
<P>
   The Rangers have made a four-year offer to Sele. They are also
interested in left-hander Chuck Finley but have yet to make an
offer, which reinforces Melvin's assertion that his first priority
is to re-sign his own free agents.
</P>
<P>
   ``We still want to try and sign a starting pitcher, but we have
to make sure we're not going crazy,'' Melvin said.
</P>
<P>
   Melvin also continues to talk with Seth Levinson, agent for
third baseman Todd Zeile. The Rangers have made an offer for two
years plus an option for a third year, and Levinson has countered
with a four-year offer.
</P>
<P>
   ``I should know more by the end of the week,'' Melvin said.
MAYORAL RESIGNS
</P>
<P>
   Rangers Spanish broadcaster Luis Mayoral is resigning after
seven years with the club. Mayoral, who is close to former Rangers
outfielder Juan Gonzalez, is expected to take a similar position
with the Detroit Tigers, the team that acquired Gonzalez last
month. The Rangers are also expected to replace Josue Perez, their
other Spanish broadcaster. But Rangers vice president-public
relations John Blake said the club will continue to broadcast a
number of games in Spanish. BRIEFLY
</P>
<P>
   _ The Rangers will conduct their annual auction to benefit their
Charity Foundation at 6 p.m. Dec. 9 at the Diamond Club at The
Ballpark in Arlington. Over 200 items will be available. For
information, call (817) 273-5187.
</P>
<P>
   _ Sele has been named the Rangers' Pitcher of the Year by the
local chapter of the Baseball Writers Association of America.
</P>
<P>
   _ Catcher Ivan Rodriguez has been named the Major League Player
of the Year by ``Baseball Digest.'' nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
