<HEADLINE>
BIG 12, COTTON LOOK TO BCS FOR CLARITY
</HEADLINE>
 BOWL-TEX (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By WENDELL BARNHOUSE 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Big 12 Conference's bowl picture could come into sharper
focus Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The Bowl Championship Series has a regularly scheduled
conference call Tuesday during which it will identify teams that it
is not considering for bowls. There are two at-large bids available
and three candidates _ Kansas State, Michigan and Tennessee.
</P>
<P>
   While it appears that Michigan and Tennessee _ both 9-2 _ will
be selected ahead of 10-1 Kansas State, Big 12 commissioner Kevin
Weiberg said last night he remains hopeful the Wildcats will land
an at-large berth. If that happens, it could mean an extra $13
million for the Big 12.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're still working diligently to make that happen,'' he said.
``If the BCS decides to release Kansas State, then we'll know we're
not getting a team in an at-large berth.''
</P>
<P>
   If that happens, Weiberg will push the Big 12 to make
contingency plans based on the outcome of Saturday's Nebraska-Texas
conference championship game. Weiberg will meet by telephone with
Big 12 athletic directors Tuesday to discuss the bowl situation.
</P>
<P>
   Weiberg said he would like for the league to start finalizing
its bowl matchups so that the teams and the bowls can start selling
tickets and making arrangements.
</P>
<P>
   The winner of the Nebraska-Texas game will get the Big 12's
automatic berth in the BCS and likely will play in the Jan. 2
Fiesta Bowl. If Texas loses, the Longhorns could play in either the
Holiday or Alamo bowls. If Nebraska loses, the Cornhuskers would
play in the Cotton Bowl, probably against Arkansas.
</P>
<P>
   If Nebraska defeats Texas, that would probably send Kansas State
to the Cotton Bowl. There have been rumors that Kansas State
officials would prefer a trip to the Holiday Bowl and would be
willing to swap places with Texas, allowing the Cotton Bowl to
stage a game between the Longhorns and the Razorbacks.
</P>
<P>
   ``My understanding is that Kansas State will be very open to
playing in the Cotton Bowl,'' Weiberg said. ``And our agreements
don't allow for that kind of a swap or deal to be made.''
</P>
<P>
   Weiberg said that Texas A&AMP;M has a chance to be selected by the
Holiday Bowl. If that happens, Texas could go to the Fiesta Bowl
with a victory in the Big 12 championship game and to the Alamo
Bowl with a loss. nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-11-30-99 0127EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
