<HEADER>
A4987 &Cx1f; tab-z
r l BC-IMMACULATE-COMPLEXION     11-30 0476
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-IMMACULATE-COMPLEXION-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IMMACULATE COMPLEXION  
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
   (To purchase this special ``one-shot'' feature from W magazine,
contact New York Times Syndicate sales representative DEBRA WEYDERT
at (732) 390-4480; fax, 732-390-4697.)  
 &HT;    
 By PATRICIA REYNOSO 
 c.1999 Fairchild Publications   
<TEXT>
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &LR;  &QC;
<P>
   With the 20th century winding to a close, what better
opportunity is there to rethink certain beauty adages?
</P>
<P>
   Everybody's favorite _ ``it's impossible to be too rich or too
thin'' _ is so obvious it's no longer appropriate. A more suitable
version? Your skin can never be too perfect.
</P>
<P>
   Perfection is a lofty goal, but thanks to innovations in the
skin-care market, it's one that is almost within reach.
</P>
<P>
   The most revered ingredient to hit your beauty cabinet is
retinol, the stabilized version of pure vitamin A that received a
lot of positive attention when it was first introduced early last
year.
</P>
<P>
   (For years now, dermatologists have been prescribing Retin-A and
Renova, the FDA-approved topical treatments that use a vitamin A
derivative for combating acne and fine wrinkles, respectively.)
</P>
<P>
   ``If you're beginning not to love what's staring at you in the
mirror, then a vitamin A product is the single best investment you
can make for yourself,'' says Dr. David E. Bank, a dermatologist
and the director of The Center for Dermatology, Cosmetic &AMP; Laser
Surgery in Mount Kisco, N.Y. Bank considers retinol products an
effective substitute for prescription treatments.
</P>
<P>
   Now the wonder ingredient is even more attainable with products
like the new L'Oreal Plenitude Line Eraser, an evening cream
featuring retinol.
</P>
<P>
   Thanks to a patented formula created by the mad scientists at
L'Oreal, Line Eraser delivers all of the benefits of vitamin A _ a
smoother and more even complexion in two weeks, significantly
diminished fine lines in four weeks _ without the irritation and
discomfort usually associated with other forms of vitamin A
products.
</P>
<P>
   According to Didier Gagnebien,, vice president of treatment and
cosmetics for L'Oreal Research and Development, creating an
effective retinol cream with none of the drawbacks was the biggest
challenge in Line Eraser's development, but completely worth the
wait.
</P>
<P>
   ``Vitamin A helps with skin-cell renewal,'' Gagnebien says. ``In
doing that, it thickens the epidermis, which is critical because
the older you get, the thinner your epidermis gets.''
</P>
<P>
   Thinner skin translates into wrinkles that are more visible to
the naked eye.
</P>
<P>
   ``Our patented formula is the perfect balance between efficacy
and tolerance,'' Gagnebien says. ``It can be used by any skin type,
every day.''
</P>
<P>
   -----
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (Patricia Reynoso is a reporter for Fairchild Publications.) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   -----
</P>
<P>
   -0-
</P>
