   PAGE INCLUDES FOUR COLOR PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   CRICHTON: A MAN IN TIME: When you watch Michael Crichton _
author of ``Jurassic Park,'' creator of TV's ``ER'' _ striding
toward you across a hotel lobby, it gives new meaning to the term
``high-concept writer.'' (Includes 2-column color photo of author
Michael Crichton.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: REVIEW: FRANKLIN: Queen of Soul Aretha Franklin fails to
get personal in her new autobiography. (Includes 6-pica color photo
of book jacket.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: REVIEW: EVEREST: ``Ghosts of Everest'' adds depth to a
romantic historical legend. (Includes 6-pica color photo of book
jacket.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: SKUBE ON BOOKS: Alistair Cooke takes the true measure of a
man's character. (Includes 1-column color photo of columnist.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: N.Y. TIMES BEST SELLERS LIST
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SCIENCE &AMP; HEALTH &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PAGE INCLUDES SEVEN COLOR PHOTOS, ONE COLOR PHOTO ILLUSTRATION
</P>
<P>
   HOLIDAY HEARTBURN: Feast sensibly during the holiday season and
you won't make an enemy of your stomach. (Page includes 4-column
color photo illustration of food and a collection of antacids.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: HEARTBURN RELIEF: A list of over-the-counter items to help
you relieve heartburn. (Includes six 1-column color photos of
antacid boxes.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: DIGESTIVE DISORDER GUIDE: A guide to some common digestive
disorders.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: SURGEONS' GOGGLES: An innovative vision device could
revolutionize the way surgeons function in the operating room.
(Includes 1-column color photo of doctor wearing goggles.)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WRESTLING (Available by 5 p.m., Wed., Dec. 1):  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TOYS: Step into the aisles of wrestling toys in local stores and
the lights seem to go just a bit dimmer. That's because you're
surrounded by black. You're surrounded by the glaring, sinister
faces of wrestling figures dressed as fiends. Psychotic murderers.
Death's heads. Many of these toys are modeled on shows that are
rated TV-14 for violence and sexual innuendo. Yet nearly all of the
toys are labeled ``for ages 4 and up.''
</P>
<P>
   TOYBOX CHECK: Is this toy good for your preschooler?
</P>
<P>
   GRAPEVINE: News and notes from the wrestling industry.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT (Available by 2 p.m., Thu., Dec. 2) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HOLIDAY MUSIC REVIEW: Jingle bells or elfin hell? You never know
what you'll get when you pop open a holiday-themed CD. Here are
some musical recommendations to help harmonize your holiday.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: VIDEO REVIEWS: Even with those roles played by Will Smith
and Kevin Kline, directed by Barry Sonnenfeld (``Men in Black'')
and lavished with a rumored $180 million budget, ``Wild, Wild
West'' is a mediocre mess. Also reviews of ``William Shakespeare's
A Midsummer Night's Dream'' and ``Simon Sez.'' (Includes an 18-pica
color photo from ``Wild, Wild West.'')
</P>
<P>
   WITH: CD REVIEWS: Korn, California's king of corrosive downer
rock, deserves credit for taking what used to be deemed ``heavy
metal'' into an altered dimension of sonic and psychic disruption.
Also reviews of the latest from Q-Tip and Alanis Morrisette.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: COMMENTARY: Network executives argue that cable channels
don't flag reruns, so why should they? With viewers abandoning the
networks in ever-increasing numbers, executives don't want to put
an exit sign over their own doors.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FOCUS (Available by 2 p.m., Fri., Dec. 3) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DIVIDED KOSOVO: In the spring, the Serbs sought to drive ethnic
Albanians from Kosovo. Since NATO troops rolled into the province,
the Albanians have been returning the favor, killing hundreds of
Serbs and burning their houses and driving them out. Now the Serbs
as well as Gypsies are a vulnerable population who live in fear of
constant reprisals. Aid workers worry that the international
community made a fatal error by treating the end of the war as a
triumph of the Albanians over the Serbs, thus creating an
environment that emboldened revenge-seeking Albanians.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: KOSOVO'S HOMELESS: As winter approaches, the task of
housing homeless in Kosovo grows daunting.
</P>
