   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   DOW-CORNING-BANKRUPCTY (Bay City, Mich.) _ A federal judge
approves Dow Corning Corp's $4.5 billion plan to emerge from
bankruptcy. The plan allocates $3.2 billion to settle claims made
by women with breast implants. Dow Corning, once the world's
largest manufacturer of silicone breast implants, filed for
bankruptcy in May 1995. By CHERYL WADE and JENNIFER CORBETT DOOREN.
</P>
<P>
   SF-MAYORAL (San Francisco) _ Tom Ammiano, president of the San
Francisco Board of Supervisors and candidate for mayor, battles
City Hall to keep intact his proposed legislation to boost the
minimum wage of thousands of low-paid workers. The measure would
require city contractors and those who lease city property to pay
their workers at least $11 an hour plus benefits, or $12 an hour
without benefits. By RACHEL GORDON.
</P>
