the border from Brownsville to the killings of 18 adults and
children in a Mexican seaside town in 1998, drug traffickers have
been killing off their rivals, informants and family members of
drug traffickers for decades. The difference is that U.S. citizens
are rarely involved. Although the bodies of U.S. citizens have been
discovered, U.S. authorities have limited authority when helping
Mexican authorities with investigations of such slayings. By MARISA
