A5275 &Cx1f; tad-z
u e BC-WASHEDUP-LIST-COX     11-30 0595
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WASHEDUP-LIST-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Where are other former prime-time soap stars working?
 &HT;    (EDS: Runs with TILTON-COX and WASHEDUP-ACTORS-COX.)
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ FALCON CREST (CBS _ 1981-90)
</P>
<P>
   Robert Foxworth: After playing ``Crest'''s Chase Gioberti until
1987, he resurfaced in '92 in the failed CBS soap ``2000 Malibu
Road.'' In 1998, he returned to Broadway opposite Jane Alexander in
``Ivanov.'' He was last seen on network TV in the NBC sitcom
``Lateline.''
</P>
<P>
   _ DALLAS (CBS _ 1978-91)
</P>
<P>
   Larry Hagman: Dressed as oil mogul J.R. Ewing, he recently
worked as a pitchman in Romania for Russian Lukoil. ``Dallas'' was
a favorite on Romanian TV. After his well-publicized liver
transplant in 1995, Hagman starred in the fast-canceled drama
``Orleans.'' Last year, he appeared in the feature film ``Primary
Colors.''
</P>
<P>
   Linda Gray: J.R. Ewing's oft-abused wife, Sue Ellen, is a
goodwill ambassador for the United Nations Population Fund. Along
with the ``Dallas'' reunion movies in '96 and '98, she last did
network series work in 1994-95, first joining the cast of ``Melrose
Place'' and then spinning off to star in the short-lived ``Models,
Inc.'' Her daughter Kehly Sloane runs her production company.
</P>
<P>
   Victoria Principal: The former Pamela Barnes Ewing did a TV
movie (''Mistress'') after she left ``Dallas'' in 1987. Produced
and starred in the TV movie ``Naked Lie'' in 1989. Tried stage work
in ``Love Letters'' (1990) and is a recurring character in The WB
network show ``Jack &AMP; Jill.''
</P>
<P>
   _ KNOTS LANDING (CBS _ 1979-93)
</P>
<P>
   Michele Lee: She backed up her acting career by writing scripts,
directing and a singing career. She rode ``Knots'' (as Karen
MacKenzie) until it dropped and then moved to TV movies. In 1996,
she co-wrote, directed and starred in the Lifetime cable movie
``Color Me Perfect.''
</P>
<P>
   Joan Van Ark: She had impressive stage credits before playing
Valene Ewing on ``Dallas''/''Knots.'' She has directed TV movies,
worked the stage in Edward Albee's ``Three Tall Women'' (1995) in
New York and ``Star Dust'' in L.A. (1997). She last appeared as
Valene Ewing in the reunion movie ``Knots Landing: Back to the
Cul-de-Sac,'' also in '97.
</P>
<P>
   Ted Shackelford: He landed a job in the Fox show ``Manchester
Prep,'' a show so bad it was canceled in October before it aired.
After playing Gary Ewing on ``Dallas''/''Knots,'' did TV movies and
guest shots on the CBS sitcom ``Cybil.''
</P>
<P>
   _ DYNASTY (ABC _ 1981-89)
</P>
<P>
   Linda Evans: She spent time in an L.A. court this summer trying
to extricate herself from two partners in 11 San Francisco-area
Linda Evans Fitness Clubs. She claimed breach of contract. After
playing Audra in ``The Big Valley'' and Krystle in ``Dynasty,''
Evans spent the past several years selling exercise stuff and
serving 10 years as the wife of new age musician Yanni. That job
ended last year. She did the '91 ``Dynasty'' reunion movie and the
'97 USA movie ``The Stepsister.''
</P>
<P>
   Joan Collins: She's still in the tabloids fighting with her
fiction-writing sister Jackie Collins. An accomplished British
stage actress long before playing evil Alexis Carrington Colby
until '89, Collins, 66, can seemingly land jobs _ stage or TV _ at
will. The tiff with Jackie is reportedly based on Joan getting a $4
million advance for two books, the second so bad that the publisher
sued to get $1.3 mil back. Alexis, um, Joan, won in court. Her last
network soap, ``Pacific Palisades,'' died a quick death in '97.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
