   FOOTBALL/COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   FBC-REFS-SUSPENDED _ The Southeastern Conference has suspended
the officials who worked last week's Georgia-Georgia Tech game in
Atlanta. (Barnhart, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   FBC-TECH-UGA _ The fallout continues from Georgia Tech's 51-48
overtime victory over Georgia. Tech head coach George O'Leary said
Tuesday ``that the better team won _ period'' and that the Georgia
folks need to learn to lose with class. (Clemons, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 14.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GATORS-KICKER _ GAINESVILLE, Fla. _ Florida placekicker Jeff
Chandler reached the lowest point of his career when he missed the
key extra-point attempt in the wild regular-season loss to Alabama.
Entering the rematch in Saturday's SEC title game, Chandler is
riding high. Since the Alabama game, Chandler has been one of the
nation's most consistent kickers. Now, he hopes to get another
chance - maybe with a game-winning field goal on the line - against
the Crimson Tide. (Towers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-BAMA-DEFENSE _ TUSCALOOSA, Ala. _ Alabama has been riding
the wave of its strong offense throughout the season, but the
Crimson Tide players believe that defense will be the key in
Saturday's SEC championship game against Florida. After allowing a
season-high 39 points to the Gators, Alabama has allowed an average
of less than 17 points in its last six games. (Arey, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18
</P>
<P>
   GASOUTHERN _ Georgia Southern has the highest scoring offense in
Division I-AA and opened the national playoffs last weekend with a
72-29 victory over Northern Arizona. Most of the publicity has gone
to standout running back Adrian Peterson, a two-time All-American.
But a lot of the responsibility falls on the shoulders of
quarterback Greg Hill, who accounted for six touchdowns against
Northern Arizona. With the Eagle defense continuing to struggle,
Hill and the offense will need another strong performance in
Saturday's quarterfinal against Massachusetts. (Reese, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL/PROS
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FALCONS _ Falcons expecting to make several roster moves to
find healthy bodies to play vs. Saints. (Winkeljohn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   HOCKEY
</P>
<P>
   HKN-CONCUSSIONS _ Nelson Emerson will likely miss two weeks
after becoming the fifth Thrashers player to suffer a concussion
this season. Concussions are becoming more common in the NHL
despite the use of helmets and other precautions. The reason is the
increased speed of the game and the size of the players. Several
players have had to retire because of post-concussion syndrome.
(Schultz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
