<HEADLINE>
HANG UP AND ENJOY YOUR DINNER
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   Rep.  &UR; Matt Salmon &LR; , R-Ariz., has introduced the Don't Disturb My
Dinner Act, which would ban telemarketers from calling households
between 5 and 7 p.m. Current law forbids such calls before 8 a.m.
or after 9 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   ``These pesky telemarketers are invading people's privacy to
begin with,'' Salmon told the Arizona Republic. ``I think we ought
to put additional limits so they don't disrupt one of the most
important times that families enjoy together. As a father of four,
I get very guarded about my time with my children. The only time I
can guarantee we can be together is dinner time.''
</P>
<P>
   Salmon says his proposed law, formally called the
``Telemarketing Victims Protection Act,'' is supported by the
American Association of Retired Persons and other consumer groups.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHAT IF &LR;
</P>
<P>
   If you've conquered your fears of jammed-up bank accounts and
disrupted plane schedules at New Year's, consider the question
posed in the press materials for ``The Worst Case Scenario Survival
Handbook'' (Chronicle Books; $14.95) by  &UR; Joshua Piven &LR;  and  &UR; David
Borgenicht &LR; : ``Does anybody really know what will happen at 12:01
a.m., January 1, 2000?''
</P>
<P>
   Among the book's solutions to situations you might fear:
</P>
<P>
   How to jump from a bridge or cliff into a river; how to wrestle
free from an alligator; how to perform a tracheotomy; and how to
escape from quicksand.
</P>
<P>
   A preface to the book warns that the authors and publishers
``disclaim any liability from the use ... of the information
contained in this book.''
</P>
<P>
   P.S. Glancing at the Federal Transit Administration calendar _
on the FTA's Web site _  &UR; Cynthia Bocoboc &LR;  isn't sure whether to be
reassured or worried. From January 11-12, there's a conference on
``Response to Chemical, Biological and Nuclear Transit Incidents'';
January 19 brings ``Threat Management and Emergency Response to Bus
Hijackings Seminar.''
</P>
<P>
   P.P.S.  &UR; Greg George &LR;  was relieved to read that Sanyo has a line
of ``Y2K compliant'' vacuum cleaners; and  &UR; Martha Stewart &LR;  has
announced that she will be serving fruit from candied grapefruit
shells just after dawn on New Year's morning. Meanwhile, the
question posed by Shape magazine: ``What does the dawn of a new
millennium mean for fitness?'' The answer: Whatever.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
