   _  &UR; Barbra Streisand &LR; 's Stickley cabinets were bought for
$125,000 on Monday by the Craftsman Farms Foundation, a nonprofit
group that had tried unsuccessfully to get her to donate them.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SAVE WATER AND STRESS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The Washington Monthly's Memo of the Month is a press release
sent to the media in mid-August, the middle of the summer drought,
by  &UR; Curtis Austin  &LR; of the Center for Mental Health Services, of the
U.S. Department of Health and Human Services. Austin recommends
three ``drought-related stress reduction activities'':
</P>
<P>
   _ Don't leave the water running when you brush your teeth, so
``you can tune in and focus more on the actual brushing.'' The
sound of the ``continually flowing water in the background ... can
be a very subtle source of agitation.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Shade your plants from the midday sun. Thinking about this and
accomplishing it allows you to spend ``time communing with nature
and learning how growth occurs.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Resist the reflexive action'' of automatically flushing for
liquid waste in the middle of the night. ``Believe it or not,
flushing itself can add to the stress of awakening in the middle of
the night because of the noise element.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``There's a wonderful exercise where you throw out a quarter, a
nickel, a dime and a penny on the table. Then you ask, `What do you
see?' When our therapist did this with us, I said, `Silver copper,
round things, change.' When he did the same thing with Tommy, he
said, `Forty-two cents.' We both have different ways of looking
things.''
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; Pamela Anderson Lee in a Jane magazine story mined for
Personals by Kate Williams, who knows how to count pennies when she
needs to.
</P>
