<HEADLINE>
BUSINESS TRAVEL: ARRANGING BUSINESS FLIGHTS VIA INTERNET 
</HEADLINE>
   (duplication notice: also sent with `f' code)  
 (bl)  
 By Jane L. Levere   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Business travelers worldwide are increasingly embracing the
Internet to research and book their flights, an annual survey by
the International Air Transport Association has found.
</P>
<P>
   Almost two-thirds of the survey's approximately 1,000
respondents from Europe, North America and the Asia-Pacific region
