   SCOTUS-SMUT (Washington) _ The Clinton administration urges the
Supreme Court to revive a law aimed at shielding children from
Playboy Television and other sexually explicit cable TV channels.
The lawyer for Playboy called the law passed by Congress three
years ago ``regulatory overkill.'' By STEVE LASH.
