   SCOTUS-MOLEST (Washington) _ Texas Attorney General John Cornyn
urges a skeptical Supreme Court to uphold the child molestation
conviction of a Texas man, even though he was found guilty based on
a girl's testimony that would have been inadmissible at the time of
the attack. By STEVE LASH.
</P>
