<HEADLINE>
HUNT FOR GRAVES DISRUPTS QUIET DESERT COUNTRYSIDE
</HEADLINE>
 (EDS: One ``c'' in Rebeca in byline is cq.) 
(Adds location of Juarez as across from El Paso, Texas) 
(For use by NYTimes News Service Clients) 
By REBECA RODRIGUEZ 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   CIUDAD JUAREZ, Mexico _ Brenda Balandran clutched her infant son
and stared at the masked men in black with rifles dangling at their
sides.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is hard to believe,'' she said. ``Imagine all this going
on in such a peaceful place.''
</P>
<P>
   Balandran, who lives in Juarez, just across the Rio Grande from
El Paso, Texas, was one of many stunned by reports that Mexican and
U.S. authorities were searching for a mass grave on a ranch south
